The first convertible bond issued by aSouth Korean firm overseas -- by Samsung Electronics Co Ltd&lt;SAMS.SE> -- became eligible for conversion but there was nodemand for shares as the government still bans direct shareownership by foreigners, a Samsung official said.    "There was no demand from holders, so the lead managers madeno approach to us to issue shares," the official said.    The five pct bond, co-lead managed by S.G. Warburg andGoldman Sachs Co, raised 20 mln dlrs when issued in 1985. Theonly other Korean convertible bonds were issued by Daewoo HeavyIndustries Ltd &lt;DAEW.SE> and &lt;Yukong Ltd>, both in 1986. REUTER&#3;